﻿React SPA
ENV: https://react.lyhin.com

Description: ﻿React SPA auth app with two jwt auth 
sign in mechanisms implemented: identity auth, google auth.

● .NET App MVC;
● React App in ReactFolder;
● ReactApp endpoint in HomeController without Layout;
● set build dir to '../wwwroot/libs';
● turn off output files hashes on build;
Note: how to start and run spa app 'live' for debugging;
- npm run build (for deployment);
- npm run dev (files are im memory);
● enabled identity;
- creds: test@test.tt / Qwerty_0;
- added login endpoint with jwt token;
- added swagger n checked authed endpoint with the token;
● add sign in demo page;
- enable jwt auth login response on sign in;
- clear jwt on logout;
- header controls: sign in button (signed out) / avatar, etc. (signed in);
- left menu controls: hide private pages;
● enabled interceptors for http requests: get users for authed;
● enable google auth: custom button;
● set db provider to sqlite;
● enable route guard for private pages;
● role authorization;

APIs:
https://localhost:8001/api/wf          Public
https://localhost:8001/api/wf/auth     Authentication: [Authorization]
https://localhost:8001/api/Users/admin Authorization:  [Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]

